Major-General Sir Arthur Wigram Money, KCB, KBE, CSI (23 October 1866 – 25 October 1951) was a British Army officer.
Money served as Chief Administrator of Palestine between June 1918 – June 1919, but was removed by London for not favoring the Zionists over the Arabs; his successor was removed six months later for the same reason.
